沙漠化現象可能是自然的。作為自然現象的沙漠化是因為地球乾燥帶移動，所產生的氣候變化導致局部地區沙漠化。不過，今日世界各地沙漠化原因，多數歸咎於人為原因；人口急速增長，所居土地被過分耕種以及牧畜，導致土地枯竭不適合耕種。沙漠化通常由自然沙漠週邊開始，進而逐漸擴散開來。研究显示，在许多环境中，随着植被覆盖增加，侵蚀和流失会成指数减少。<ref>{{cite book|authors=Geeson, Nichola|title=Mediterranean desertification: a mosaic of processes and responses|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2002|isbn=978-0-470-84448-9|page=58|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G_0qg0f49GQC&pg=PA58|display-authors=etal|access-date=2017-08-06|archive-date=2016-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161204063024/https://books.google.com/books?id=G_0qg0f49GQC&pg=PA58|dead-url=no}}</ref>暴露的旱地土壤会被风吹走或被洪水冲走，留下贫瘠土地在日光下暴晒，变成不毛之地。艾伦·萨弗瑞（Allan Savory）则给出有争议的意见，认为控制牲畜，模拟野生牧群可以逆转沙漠化。<ref>{{cite web|last=Savory|first=Allan|title=Allan Savory: How to green the world's deserts and reverse climate change|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vpTHi7O66pI|accessdate=2017-08-06|archive-date=2015-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150915014215/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vpTHi7O66pI|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Savory|first=Allan|title=Holistic resource management: a conceptual framework for ecologically sound economic modelling|url=http://www.savoryinstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/ISEE_economic_modeling_paper.pdf|work=Ecological Economics|publisher=Elsevier Science Publishers|accessdate=10 March 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523200348/http://www.savoryinstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/ISEE_economic_modeling_paper.pdf|archivedate=2013年5月23日}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Butterfield|first=Jody|title=Holistic Management Handbook: Healthy Land, Healthy Profits, Second Edition|year=2006|publisher=Island Press|isbn=1559638850}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Savory|first=Allan|title=Response to request for information on the "science" and "methodology" underpinning Holistic Management and holistic planned grazing|url=http://www.savoryinstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Science-Methodology-Holistic-Mgt_Update_March.pdf|work=Savory Institute|accessdate=10 March 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523074713/http://www.savoryinstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Science-Methodology-Holistic-Mgt_Update_March.pdf|archivedate=2013年5月23日}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Drury|first1=Steve|title=Large-animal extinction in Australia linked to human hunters|url=http://earth-pages.co.uk/2012/04/13/large-animal-extinction-in-australia-linked-to-human-hunters/|publisher=Earth-Pages|accessdate=9 June 2014|archive-date=2017-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806181659/https://earth-pages.co.uk/2012/04/13/large-animal-extinction-in-australia-linked-to-human-hunters/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==历史==
世界上最著名的[[荒漠|荒漠]]是长时间自然形成的。在绝大多数时间里，沙漠变大变小，与人为活动无关。古老的大型[[沙漠|沙漠]]有些如今被植被控制，已经不再活跃，有些跨越現今的核心区域，如最大最热的[[撒哈拉沙漠|撒哈拉沙漠]]。<ref name="Desertification">United States Geological Survey, [http://pubs.usgs.gov/gip/deserts/desertification/ "Desertification"] {{Wayback|url=http://pubs.usgs.gov/gip/deserts/desertification/ |date=20100802200740 }}, 1997</ref>

沙漠化在人类历史上角色重要，导致数个大型帝国崩溃，如迦太基、希腊和罗马帝国，并使得当地人口迁徙转移。<ref name="Geist-2005-p4" /><ref name="LOWDERMILK">{{cite web|last=LOWDERMILK|first=W C|title=CONQUEST OF THE LAND THROUGH SEVEN THOUSAND YEARS|url=http://www.nrcs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb1043789.pdf|work=Soil Conservation Service|publisher=United States Department of Agriculture|accessdate=9 April 2014|archive-date=2017-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170807235242/https://www.nrcs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb1043789.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Whitford, Walter G.|title=Ecology of desert systems|publisher=Academic Press|year=2002|isbn=978-0-12-747261-4|page=277|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OZ4hZbXS8IcC&pg=PA277|access-date=2017-08-07|archive-date=2019-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614213045/https://books.google.com/books?id=OZ4hZbXS8IcC&pg=PA277|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Bogumil Terminski (2011), Towards Recognition and Protection of Forced Environmental Migrants in the Public International Law: Refugee or IDPs Umbrella, Policy Studies Organization (PSO), Washington.</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Geist|first=Helmut|title=The causes and progression of desertification|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=acbWdynlU3cC&pg=PA4&lpg=PA4&dq=desertification+and+its+effect+on+ancient+civilisations&source=bl&ots=5kLznD1bv-&sig=pd8eodCyZuBl_KH4MQHyfx9QKsY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=gVHYUfnIM4bmigLAzoHwCw&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=desertification%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20ancient%20civilisations&f=false|work=Antony Rowe Ltd|publisher=Ashgate publishing limited|accessdate=6 July 2013|archive-date=2019-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614125421/https://books.google.com/books?id=acbWdynlU3cC#v=onepage&q=desertification%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20ancient%20civilisations&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>历史迹象显示几个世纪前干旱区域严重的、大规模的土地退化发生在三个人口稠密的中心：地中海地区、美索不达米平原和中国[[黄土高原|黄土高原]]。<ref name="LOWDERMILK"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Dregne|first=H.E.|title=Desertification of Arid Lands|url=http://www.ciesin.columbia.edu/docs/002-193/002-193.html|publisher=Columbia University|accessdate=3 December 2013|archive-date=2017-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810214952/http://www.ciesin.columbia.edu/docs/002-193/002-193.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[中東|中東]]的[[美索不達米亞|美索不達米亞]]（今[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]）地區是世上最早發展[[農業|農業]]的地域之一，從而發展成世上最早的文明發祥地之一。美索不達米亞的土壤本來甚為肥沃，不過由於過度的農業活動，人們不理會土地長期枯渴，更開發河段上游、採伐森林，上游土地從而不能吸收降雨，雨水全都流入河中造成水土流失以及[[洪水|洪水]]。

==受影响地区==
